        <description>
This small MSX-1 computer is quite original. It is very compact and 
was marketed has a handheld computer ! Thus, there is a handle which
 is pulled out from the front of the machine.
There are two cartridge ports and the power unit 
could be attached or not to the back of the system (see picture).

Apparently the H1 had built-in graphic and music software, hence the graphic tablet available (see hardware section).

There was also a smaller version called H1E which had only 16 kb of RAM.
 


